![no_std]\r\n#![feature(alloc)]\r\n\r\nextern crate alloc;\r\n\r\nuse alloc::alloc::Layout;\r\n\r\nfn allocate(size: usize) -> *mut u8 {\r\n    unsafe { alloc::alloc::alloc(Layout::from_size_align(size, 32).unwrap()) }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n- [Playground in 2018](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=150a82a89e210f0effb30247ad987e50)\r\n- [Playground in 2015](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2015&gist=20ee51c55df7206274015d5a8c24aa6c)\r\n\r\nHowever if I add a `self::` prefix to the `use` statement, it compiles in both edition:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![no_std]\r\n#![feature(alloc)]\r\n\r\nextern crate alloc;\r\n\r\nuse self::alloc::alloc::Layout;\r\n\r\nfn allocate(size: usize) -> *mut u8 {\r\n    unsafe { alloc::alloc::alloc(Layout::from_size_align(size, 32).unwrap()) }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n- [Playground in 2018](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=3094c30526eedcd0fbe4ff616a25571d)\r\n\r\nI do not know why I need to add `self::` when using 2018 edition. My apologies if this is an expected behavior. (On a side note, is there a better way to use `alloc::alloc::alloc`? The crate, module and function being the same name is kind of ridiculous \ud83d\ude1b )", "closed_by": {"login": "steveklabnik", "id": 27786, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI3Nzg2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/27786?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", 